items.headline: Welcome to the Music Wiki!
items.desc:
The Music Wiki is a wiki devoted to creating the definitive music encyclopedia which includes aspects of all music topics.

From artists to labels, to the songs themselves we are a resource for every aspect of the music business. All genres! All artists! All sounds! Whatever your preference, we aim to provide the definitive subculture soundtrack.

items.name: Philly Music Wiki
items.title: Philly Music Wiki
items.headline: Everything about current bands and musicians in Philadelphia.
items.desc: Wikipedia itself is far too large and regulated (and rightly so) to have a page dedicated to every band, musician, and release that ever existed. The Philly Music Wiki aims to fill that void by providing a centralized repository of all information pertaining to the current-day music scene in Philadelphia and the surrounding area.

items.name: 4chanmusic Wiki
items.title: 4chanmusic Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the 4chan Music Wiki.
items.desc: The 4chan music wiki is a wiki dedicated to all things relating to 4chan's /mu/ board and music-related information. Charts provided here are to be used as an entry-point into a genre, allowing you to gain a basic understanding of what a genre could have to offer. It is recommended that you explore genres on your own after having listened through some of the recommended music. The best way of receiving recommendations on /mu/ is by making conversation with people in threads and then just asking what they would recommend.

items.name: Club Penguin Music Wiki
items.title: Club Penguin Music Wiki
items.headline: The Club Penguin Music Wiki!
items.desc: On the Club Penguin Music Wiki, you can learn about all the music in Club Penguin!  All you have to do to contribute is to add the SWF (Shockwave Flash) link(s) to the pages and then we can look for the music. The Wiki has many articles and is looking for more music in Club Penguin.  What are you waiting for? Get started at club-penguin-music.wikia.com  . Note: Due to the nature of Adobe Flash Player, audio SWFs can NOT be played on mobiles/tablets. Please use the desktop version of the wiki instead.

items.name: ElectricMusic Wiki
items.title: ElectricMusic Wiki
items.headline: Sounds Great,EDM, One Place! Electric Music WIki(EDM & More)
items.desc:
I'm Nathan Leachman, and this is my Wiki. Got Music? 

Wait, let me rephrase that...Got EDM?!

An EDM listener of all kinds, I would like to teach you the new age of music! You may be hesitant to listen to something that is a bunch of random sounds made on a computer, but that's not EDM!

Oh, I'm sorry I mean that's not all of EDM! EDM can range from pop-culture mixes. 

DO you know that the song "Avicii - Wake Me Up ft. Aloe Black" hmm? That has a country, pop, theme in one song. That song is considered an EDM...Many famous DJ's are EDM Producers and you didn't even know it. Avicii, Swedish House Mafia, Calvin Harris...So, don't judge a book by it's cover...However, if it's just not for you, that's fine too.

We have a live chat that you can talk about anything, sections in our forums where you can bring up the style of music you like. Or if you want to just be informed, that's cool too!

...Also, we are trying to do things unique. Like are top 10 artists list, tips & blogs on production, and several songs you can jam out to! We will always be active & updating and such. With some of the most detailed thing...

One thing, we are a new wiki. And We NEED You! In order to make this an amazing Wiki, I can not do this myself. So I need your help/support and contribute in every way you can!
